                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-208-off1172 t18320906-208-crimeloc1175"></join>. On the 31st of August, about five o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoner came into the shop and asked for a halfpenny pen; he put down sixpence, and I gave him a pen and 5 1/2d. - he stood at the counter; I was making up my accounts, and this money was on the counter - immediately I gave him the pen, I saw him snatch the five sovereigns out of the bowl; he got out of the shop, but was caught by two officers, without my losing sight of him - he fell on the ground, and the three sovereigns were under him; the other two were never found - I asked what he had done with the other two; he said the man who had picked the others up, was as likely to have them as him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-208-person1735">
                  RICHARD 
                  COWDEROY
               <interp inst="t18320906-208-person1735" type="surname" value="COWDEROY"></interp>
